# Experiment 4
## List and Related Functions in Python

### Aim
To write a Python program to demonstrate list operations and related functions.

### Algorithm
1. Start the program.
2. Create a list with some elements.
3. Display the list.
4. Add an element to the list using append().
5. Insert an element at a specific position using insert().
6. Remove an element using remove().
7. Sort the list using sort().
8. Display the updated list.
9. Stop the program.

Source Code
list=["cloud computing","deployment","cloud model","info security","service models","IaaS",
      "PaaS","SaaS","cloud infrastructure","storage","databases","internet","networking",
      "serverless","aws","azure","google cloud","backup","virtual","development","testing",
      "big data analysis","AI/ML","cloud security","cost efficient"]
list1=["csit","bca","ctis","da"]
my_list=list1.copy()
print("original list\n",list)
print("another list\n",list1)
print("copied list\n",my_list)
list.append("ITH")
print("after append:\n",list)
list.insert(2,"IOT")
print("after insert:\n",list)
list.pop(3)
print("after pop:\n",list)
print("index of IaaS:",list.index("IaaS"))
print("count of internet:",list.count("internet"))
list.extend([list+list1])
print("after extend:\n",list)
list.remove("cloud infrastructure")
print("after remove:\n",list)
print(list[1:6])
print("length of list:",len(list))
list.clear()
print("after clearing list\n",list)

